I don't get the point in going through anyone for your website name.The point is that they provide DNS resolution that can't be shut down by K-SLURs. So instead of your ISP or Joogle or some other K-SLUR owned organization providing you domain name resolution to IPs, it's on an immutable database. So if I wanted to register "fuckN-SLURs.andK-SLURs" as a domain and have it work even against censorship at the DNS level, that's the only option to do it.The amount of people who know how to use HOSTS to manually create their own local DNS is vanishingly small. Having an uncensorable, easy to use DNS record storage is obviously useful. It's also an obviously better scenario for everyone to have F-SLUR.N-SLURs to point to the same site instead of it being based on whatever the person involved in editing their HOSTS file wanted to point it to, because the latter is rife for abuse by K-SLUR organizations.E.g., Joogle or the user's shitlib friend says "don't worry we have an uncensored DNS, goy" and then they point F-SLUR.N-SLURs to some honeypot fake site with shit about how great N-SLURs and K-SLURs are, that's an undesirable outcome.The end user of it doesn't have to own any cryptocurrency or pay anything, only the person that created the domain does.
